                        role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">E. G. Browne</persName> together with
                     the lithographed Bombay edition of the Traveller's Narrative (see <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_627">F. 56 (BBA.
                        1)</ref> for the fuller account of this parcel, sent by an unnamed Persian
                     Bábí correspondent of Jewish extraction), "since this article went to press"
                     per Browne's own note - hence Browne's creation of this supplementary fifth,
                     "BBS," class for it, received in 1892.</provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1936">Passed to <placeName>Cambridge</placeName> University
                     Library in <date when="1936">1936</date> (the "Browne
                     Bequest").</acquisition>
               </history>
